medical_history.chief_complaint: Lower abdominal pain, absent breast development, primary amenorrhea, and multicystic ovaries.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient presented at the age of 15 with lower abdominal pain due to multicystic ovaries and was noted to have absent breast development and primary amenorrhea. Since then, she has had no complaints of abdominal pain, though her ovaries have remained enlarged with cysts.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient has a homozygous mutation, c.112G -> T (p.Gln375His) in the ESR1 gene.
medical_history.family_history: Her parents were indicated to be 2nd degree relatives supporting consanguinity.
